No, the stream is not auto closed on performing the stream pipeline operation in such cases and in fact as stated in [the documentation](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/io/BufferedReader.html#lines--) there are also *no guarantees that the reader will be at a specific position from which to read the next character or line.*

In short `Stream`s ([tag:java-stream]) are not responsible for manipulating the stream ([tag:stream]) that has been passed on for processing as a resource. Hence the preferred way to ensure auto-closable streams in such a case would be using *try-with-resource* approach as follows :

    try (InputStream stream = request.getEntity().getContent();
         BufferedReader bufferedReader = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(stream))) {
