The input file stream maintains the position of the next read location.  This position is advanced for each read transaction (unless there is an error or at end of the file).  The read position may be changed using the `seekg` method.  

This can be illustrated by reading any text file:  

    char c;
    while (text_file.read(&amp;c, 1))
    {
        std::cout &lt;&lt; c &lt;&lt; &quot;    &quot; &lt;&lt; text_file.tellg() &lt;&lt; &quot;\n&quot;;
    }

The `tellg` method returns the *read* position within the stream.

